Vice President Yemi Osinbajo took charge today at the Federal Executive Council meeting in the absence of President Muhammadu Buhari, who is away to Damaturu Yobe state on a sympathy visit. On 19 February, Boko Haram terrorists stole 110 female students of the Government Girls Science and Technical College, Dapchi. President Buhari visits the state today to assure the parents and the people of the state on the efforts being made to free the girls, unscathed. President Buhari had also visited, Taraba, Benue and Adamawa states, where there had been incidents of violence in recent times.